    },
    {
      "pos": [
        11172,
        11226
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a id=\"doityourself\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Do-it-yourself authentication"
    },
    {
      "content": "You can run an authentication framework such as <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ASP.NET Identity<ept id=\"p1\">](http://www.asp.net/identity)</ept> or <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Thinktecture<ept id=\"p2\">](http://www.thinktecture.com/identityAndAccessControl)</ept> on Azure.",
      "pos": [
        11228,
        11405
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This gives you control over how everything works, but you also have to spend more time developing and testing authentication functionality.",
      "pos": [
        11406,
        11545
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Also, if you have multiple apps to protect with multiple redirect URLs, you have to configure multiple client IDs and client secrets with third-party authentication providers such as Facebook, Google, and Twitter.",
      "pos": [
        11546,
